               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Rawḍat al-aḥbāb fī siyar al-Nabī wa-al-āl wa-al-aṣḥāb by Dashtakī, ʻAṭāʼ Allāh ibn Faḍl Allāh, -1400 or 1401&gt;
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="CODRINGTON.READE_NO_19_BOX_9-item1">
                     <author ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/16882481" key="person_16882481">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Dashtakī, ʻAṭāʼ Allāh ibn Faḍl Allāh, -1400 or 1401&gt;</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">دشتکی، عطا الله بن فضل</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1946">Rawḍat al-aḥbāb fī siyar al-Nabī wa-al-āl wa-al-aṣḥāb</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1946">روضة الاحباب في سير النبي والآل والاصحاب</title>
                     <note>Part of Maqsad 1. Bound with Codrington/Reade No 51, which it precedes. Front flyleaf, recto: In pencil, title and catalogue numbers. Slip cut from Morley's printed catalogue pasted in, with description of No XXXVIII (Codrington/Reade No 51). Folio 1, recto: In ink: David Price; In Arabic script titles and notes of purchase. One recording purchase by Husain 'Ali, another purchase at Akbarabad. Labels on spine: leather: R.A.S, P. CAT. 38. Paper: Habib-es-Siyar Vol. 2.a.; now detached: Persian 49; 19. The same work as No 18, but incomplete, breaking off in the events of A.H. 5 (A.D. 626?). [Not year 4] Iluminated first page. Ruled margins on first 64 folios. Rubricated headings, Arabic quotations etc.</note>
                     <incipit>as Codrington/Reade No 18.</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 18.</bibl>
                        <bibl>For Price's bequest see the Journal for 1836, pp. xii-xiv (an obituary note p. lx).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
